features: Efficient and Convenient: Expand your laptop's capabilities with sleek and compact aluminum alloy laptop docking station, featuring 7 versatile ports for your connectivity needs, Experience the ultimate in convenience and performance with our premium hdmi adapter for dual monitors

HD Triple Display: USB C dock boost your productivity with our advanced technology design, which includes 2 HDMI+VGA ports supporting up to 3 external monitors, so you don’t have to go back and forth between programs or files, single use HDMI1 can up to 4K 60Hz under DP1.4 source. Perfect for professionals and creatives who demand the best. *NOTE: Due to the limitation of macOS itself, all extended screen content will be the same.

Stable and Fast Transmission: USB hub streamline your workflow with fast data transfer speeds enabled by the USB 3.0 port, and connect your peripherals with 2 additional USB 2.0 ports. Maximum 87W output with the docking station' usb-c power deliver port, fully charges your laptop in a snap. *NOTE: Power adapter and input cable are not included.

Small Size and Powerful Chip: Dual monitor adapter with an intelligent chip inside ensures stability, connectivity and safety during operation, and ultra-small size makes it much easier to carry around for commuting and traveling.

Widely Compatible: This usb c hub works well with Thunderbolt 3/4 devices and most USB-C devices(Note: Some device's USB-C port does not support the video output function, when the HDMI/VGA port of docking station is used, the indicator of the hdmi hub will flash)

Checking Your DisplayPort (DP) Version: If you're using a Windows device, you can know which version of DP you have by checking your CPU generation. DP version 1.2 if your CPU is Intel generation 10 or earlier.DP version 1.4 if your CPU is Intel generation 11 or later.DP version 1.4 if you're using a workstation laptop with an NVIDIA GPU. If you're using a MacBook, iMac, or iPad, you can find your DP version from the list below: DP 1.4: iPad Pro (3rd generation and later), MacBook Pro ( 2017, 2019, 2020, 2021), MacBook Air (2020), MacBook Air (13-inch, M1, 2020), iMac (2017 and later), iMac Pro (2017 and later)DP 1.2: iPad Air (4th generation), MacBook Air (2018), MacBook Pro (2016), Mac mini (2018) *Note About Display on macOS System: macOS only support SST (Single-Stream Transport). And macOS and iPadOS don't support MST(Multi-Stream Transport) due to the limitation of macOS System itself.

How can I judge if the docking station is compatible with my device? Please make sure that your laptop's USB-C port is fully functional(Power Delivery+Data Transfer+DisplayPort Alt Mode), or you will not be able to expand some function normally. If you are not sure, please let us know before purchasing. Does it support MST On MacBook？ Due to the restriction of macOS itself, all extended screen will be the same. But our docking station is still compatible with MacBook, in the expansion mode, at most one different screen content can be realized, such as A+B+B+B. Does the indicator light help? The indicator light can help identify whether the USB-C port of the laptop supports the display output. If not, the indicator light will start to flash when using the HDMI/VGA port. Do I need to install the driver to use the HDMI adapter? No, just plug and use.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 17, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Not great when you have 3 monitors
reviews.reviewText: This is the second product I bought from this company and I was adding another monitor to my work station (3 total). While it does work, the third screen becomes small and blurry and harder to work with. This is only when this docking station is used, my monitor works great otherwise. Like I said, it may only be due to the third screen being added so this device may not fully support this many monitors in use.

reviews.reviewTitle: Adds extra ports for the IPad Pro. The one USB C port on the Pro just isn’t enough.
reviews.reviewText: I really like the IPad Pro but the one USB C port just doesn’t cut it. If you are charging your Pro then you can’t use it for anything else. Adding the docking station is straightforward and means you can change the Pro and connect to other devices at the same time. The card slots are useful for moving files or viewing photos and I use the HDMI connector regularly. The only downside is the ports are not compatible with all devices. For example the HDMI port works seamlessly with my Samsung smart tv but refuses to play with a slightly older LG.
